    "body": "@iurimatias @jrainville @alexandraB99 One thing to note - the animation shown in this video is supposed to be shown **after** all the other loading animations are completed e.g. at the point today where the user would be landed into the app.  Instead of landing the user into the app, we add an additional 30second delay (during which we show this loading bar and fun info messages) to let things load from waku in the background.  Then when the user is landed in the app, the app has already been running for 30 seconds post-user login.  This means things won't be jumping around and loading in for the first 20 or so seconds after the user initially lands in the app",
