    "body": "> Instead of landing the user into the app, we add an additional 30second delay (during which we show this loading bar and fun info messages) to let things load from waku in the background. Then when the user is landed in the app, the app has already been running for 30 seconds post-user login.\r\n\r\nAn update to whoever is going to work on this, we already have this on the backend side and use it for recovering an existing account (via seed phrase or keycard) so what would we need in this case is to move all onboarding flows to that backend logic and add on the UI side loading bar and fun info messages. (Once this is done, please check all possible onboarding flows before merging this.)\r\n\r\nBut personally I don't like at all that kind of faking/masking the things. We set it up to 30secs, but what would happen to those who has weak pc configuration or a slow internet connection and need more time? They will still see loading animation freeze. \r\n",
